{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_jamaica_ver02/data/sn83030214/00175039314/1908033001/0615.xml":{"full_text":"NEW-YORK DAILY TRIBUNE, MONDAY, MARCH 30, 1908.\nNEW-YORK DAILY TRIBUNE, MON\nRailroad Systems of\nthe United States\n10\nWe are preparing a series of Booklets\nGeseribing the important railroad sys\ntens of the United States, and show\ning their progress and development\nfrom their earliest days to the present\ntime.\nA\nThe first of this series of Booklets\n\u00a3ully deseribes the \u2018\u2018Reading System\u2019\u2019\nand gives a comparison of earnings for\nthe past ten years.\nCory of this booklet will Fe sent to\nany address upon request.\n1 he the \u201cT'nion\n(The next of this series wil\nPacific System\u2122)\nPotter, Choate Prentice\nMembers New York Stock Fxchange\nBANKERS\nHanover Bank Bullding\nTel 1560 Rector\nNEW YORK\nTel 1569 Rector NRADOGYES Daa amie\nNEW YORK\nTREATISE ON OPTIONS.\n\nMr. Arthur Cramp, iste City Editor of The Timea\n\u201cOptions\u201d as\n\u201cThe most scientific and prudent way of\ncperating on the Stock Exchenge.\u201d\nThiz system, although very popalar on the Continent\nan? in America, is not so well known amongst In\nwestors as its merits justify.\nWe heave just published a new Treatise om this\nsubject, which will be sent post free on application te\nThe Secretary.\ni.ondon &ParisExchange,Lid.\nBANKERS.\nBasildon House, Bank,\nLonden, England.\nOs from any of its Branches.\nA\nHew York City\nBonds\n\n\"WN. HARRIS CO.\nBANKERS\nPine Street, Corner Willlam\nNEW YORK\nR. L. DAY CO,\n37 Wali St., 2335 Congress St\nNEW YORE BOSTON\nFIER ERIDE IRVESTMERT BONDS\nMunicipz! ane Railroad\nMembers New York and\nBoston \u201cTuom Exchanges\nWe are offering at 20 a First Mortgage 6\u00b0\nbend on 2 coz! property excellently located for\nthe profitable marketing cf ils product. A sink\ning fund provisicn in the mortgage will take\ncare of the whole issue by 1220.\n\n\n\n\nWrite for descriptive circular.\nSWARTWOUT APPERZELLAR,\nan